race.comment: WAEREA (5) is a promising colt back from an 18-week spell. Raced twice in the maiden campaign and met with narrow defeats on each occasion in similar races to this. Trialled well over 1106m at Canterbury recently which suggests he is ready to run well. COCO DIOR (11) battled on fairly but was never a threat when resuming over 1250m at Canterbury recently. Better placed out to this trip and in a moderate provincial maiden can improve sharply. BARRENGARRY (4) returns from a 15-week spell following a so-so debut at Nowra. Now a gelding and trialled impressively here recently so one to keep very safe. AURORA EFFECT (10) has not been sighted since a decent fourth on debut over this trip at Hawkesbury in September. Nicely drawn and might have more to offer with the race experience now on board. WAKING RESOURCES (6) gets a few key gear changes today after a mediocre debut - certainly worth another chance.
